# Implementation

- ds4_rocm.c: ROCM_DEFINE_MOE_GATE_UP_IQ2XXS_WAVE(8) and
  ROCM_DEFINE_MOE_DOWN_Q2K_WAVE(8) macros define wave-per-row kernels.
- One 32-lane wave per output row, 8 rows per block (blockDim=256).
- IQ2_XXS gate_up: each lane handles (nb*8/32) ib32 sub-blocks across the row,
  computing both gate and up dots in the same loop (shared activation reads).
- Q2_K down: each lane handles (nb*16/32) quarter-blocks across the row,
  iterating over all n_used active experts before final wave-shuffle reduction.
- Reduction via rocm_wave32_sum (existing __shfl_down helper).
- Dispatch in rocm_moe_run gates on (gate_type==up_type==IQ2_XXS) for gate_up
  and (down_type==Q2_K) for down; falls back to generic kernel otherwise.

